import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Miles_per_Gallon', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['Miles_per_Gallon'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['Miles_per_Gallon'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Miles_per_Gallon?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Miles_per_Gallon')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Horsepower', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['Horsepower'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median = {:.2f}'.format(data['Horsepower'].median()))
    plt.xlabel('Engine Horsepower')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of engine horsepower?')
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.countplot(x="Origin", data=data, palette="Set2")
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, horizontalalignment='right')
    chart.set_xlabel("Car Origin")
    chart.set_ylabel("Count")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of car origins in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
